title: Do you too think Jisoo from BlackPink is just too underrated? - Quora

response.answer_text: Question: Do you think Jisoo from Blackpink is just too underrated? I don't think Jisoo from Blackpink is underrated at all. Let's look at this for a moment.  1)Her Instagram  As you can see, out of all the girls Jisoo does have the least amount of followers but she still has a lot of you compare it to other idols. I've also noticed that there's very few Jisoo stans on Instagram. Even though she has the least out of Blackpink, she still has a huge following considering the fact that she doesn't post much and she has less fans on Instagram. 2)Her popularity has gained massively since debut era This just comes from my observations but during debut Jisoo has a lot more popularity now than say around the time when Boombayah or Whitsle era. 2.1) Improvement in dancing ability and live stability Jisoo used to be mediocre at singing and her dancing was stiff and I think she just seemed boring to the public. She was criticized a lot but over the years, she really improved in her dancing and she's the most stable member now. Not to mention, a lot of people are appreciating her lovely deep voice. 2.2)Her genuine personality I personally really don't agree with people calling her the only real one in Blackpink but it's being said a lot nowadays. Over the years, many people have fallen for her silly, playful simple and fun personality and people call the rest of Blackpink fake and comment that they can't stand the rest of them. Which brings me to my next point - 2.3)Dislike towards the other members Around dx4 era, Jennie got massive hate for being lazy and unprofessional. She was also called 'rude' when she was on variety shows. Rosé became the target of MR removed videos and she also got a lot of backlash for being very unstable singing live. Lisa is still really popular but aot of people claimed she was overrated as a dancer and rapper. Jennie, Rosé and Lisa all got hate for using too much aegyo and being apperently ‘fake’. 3)She's definitely the most popular outside the blink fandom         I didn't reveal the usernames or profile picture s of any off the people who wrote these comments but I can assure that they were all people from different fandoms. As you can see, even by people who hate on Blackpink, they admit that Jisoo is the most loved outside the blink fandom and there are a lot of people who are part of other fandoms but they solo stan Jisoo. There are so many more comments but I can't put them all here or it'd be a book.  So based on everything I've said, I'd conclude that Jisoo is not underrated. While she's the least popular out of Blackpink, her popularity is growing at a rapid rate and her talents are being recognised. Like I've said, she's the most popular Blackpink member outside of the fandom too.  -chérry

response.answer_text: Definitely not. some ppl literally say she is the most talented member of blackpink. no offense, i love jisoo to bits, but she is by far the least talented of bp. so many “jisoo stans” just use the fact that they solo stan her as an excuse to hate on the other members. some things “jisoo stans aka bp antis often say” • she is the best vocalist of bp - if u read anything by someone who actually knows any basics about vocal techniques can tell u she is the weakest in the vocal line. ppl often praise her live vocals but honestly they don't stand out as absolutely amazing stability. in bp she is seen as stable, but she is around the same level or maybe below jimin who is notoriously known for being the least stable member of bts. plus she is often extremely straining, goes out of tune, cracks and is very nasally. if u want me to link a voice analysis just ask in the comments. • “she is a better dancer then jennie” gosh most of the ppl who say this are hypocrites. they say about how jisoo is amazing *now* and compare it to lazy Jennie ages ago. back when the jennie lazy scandal was going on, jisoo was still pretty bad. so when someone says Jennie is better, they bring up the lazy thing. but when someone points out that jisoo back then was also bad, they get pissed and say how *now* jisoo is good. make ur mind up. either compare both old Jennie & jisoo, or both new jennie & jisoo. i hope i explained that well idk if i did tho. so no, she is not underrated. i think some, overhype her talent a little bit. ps. she one of the most popular members in korea and globally, its starting to go like this lisajisoojennierosé

Do you too think Jisoo from BlackPink is just too underrated? I don't, I think Jisoo is regarded perfectly. I think Rosė is underrated and unfairly attacked over her voice and not fully appreciated for her dancing. I think Jennie is often rudely treated (except for that unacceptable lapse of laziness). And Lisa is too often the subject of “is she better at dancing than Momo,” even though I've taken part in that myself. But Jisoo is dead on. She is clearly the least when in comes to Blackpink's dancing, though she's gotten better. I think she is the least in the vocal line, but that doesn't make her bad. In fact, I LOVE her voice. It's deep and different and fits perfectly with the group. I heard her crack badly during a concert, but nobody's flawless, so whatever. The thing is, she tries hard. With so many English speakers in their group, she doesn't need to make effort there, but she tries anyway. Her dancing improvements means she tries. And she is easily the funniest on the team, so her charisma is tight. She gets no hate there. And she's the prettiest. There's that.  On top of it all, she has repeatedly acted as a team leader on a team that has no leader. Maybe she gets no respect for that. No, I think Jisoo is appreciated for all the right things and I see her getting few criticisms. Jisoo might be the one member who flies lowest below the radar. Thanks for reading.

You seem to be one of those 12-year-old Blinks who think that Jisoo gets mistreated and whatnot by YG. Before moving on, let me make this clear for you: she isn’t. If Jisoo was mistreated, she would be unhappy. And if she was unhappy, it would show in her Vlives and photos. Jisoo is happy, which means that Jisoo is not being mistreated — or, at least, Jisoo doesn’t feel like she’s being mistreated. And if Jisoo doesn’t feel like she’s being mistreated, you should stop whining about it. (What, did you really thing that YG was going to see that comment you wrote on a Youtube video demanding more lines for Jisoo? You wish.) Furthermore, when you say “underrated”, you mean that people aren’t appreciating her “true value”. However, Jisoo’s “true value” varies from person to person, because each person sees her differently. In my eyes, she’s just another Kpop idol. But in yours, she may mean the world. Can you force me to think differently? No, but you can try to show me why you think that she’s so amazing. I don’t want to be forced to like Jisoo. I want to like Jisoo on my own accord. The only reason why I can’t appreciate any of her qualities is because so many people try to push them onto me, and it was to the point where I just completely lost interest in Blackpink (as a group) and decided to solely support Jennie. Not everyone will see Jisoo the same way you do. Get used to it.

Let’s be real: nobody from Blackpink is underrated. There the second most popular kpop group in the world. Just because Jisoo is the least popular in within the group, doesn’t mean that she is underrated. She is widely regarded as one of the best visuals in kpop from both Korean fans and International fans. For an idol to be underrated, I think they need to be quite talented yet not that popular. Jisoo is the opposite: she isn’t overly talented nor is she unpopular. Her strong suit is her visuals, which are highly praised. Her vocals are solid but she gets even more hype from Blinks. Her dancing is negligible and she doesn’t rap. So overall, Jisoo isn’t the most talented idol. I think people are getting this “Jisoo is underrated” sentiment because she often gets the least lines in Blackpink songs. However, Blackpink songs for the most part have decent line distributions, especially compared to other groups. In conclusion, Jisoo is not underrated.
